This repository contains an official implementation of the paper:
    A Fair Empirical Risk Minimization with Generalized Entropy
    https://arxiv.org/abs/2202.11966

---

REQUIREMENTS

- Python 3.8+
- g++ supporting C++11

---

USAGE

1. Install dependencies

    python -m pip install .

2. Run example experiments

    python main.py --preset adult --alpha 0.0 --alpha 1.0 --alpha 2.0 --c 8.0 8.5 9.0 --a 5.0 --gamma "np.linspace(0.02, 0.07, 20)" --nu 0.01 --lambda_max 20.0
    python main.py --preset adult --plot_convergence --alpha 0.0 --alpha 1.0 --alpha 2.0 --gamma 0.04 --c 8.0 8.5 9.0 --a 5.0 --nu 0.01 --lambda_max 20.0

3. Then the outputs will be saved in `./output/` directory.

Type `main.py -h` for more options.
Take a look at `plot.ipynb` for API usages and plotting.
If you want a more minimal example instead of `main.py`, take a look at `mini.ipynb`.

---

NOTE

- This code is not optimized for space efficiency. It may require a lot of memory.
- Running time varies depending on the parameters. It may take a few seconds to an hour.
- Feel free to leave an issue if you have any questions.
